1
00:00:50,566 --> 00:00:52,605
(All people, organizations, locations, and incidents...)

2
00:00:52,606 --> 00:00:54,405
(in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:57,176 --> 00:00:58,575
(I'll go back to where I belong.)

4
00:01:06,285 --> 00:01:07,416
Do you mean this?

5
00:01:09,056 --> 00:01:10,155
I do.

6
00:01:11,015 --> 00:01:12,385
Why did you change your mind?

7
00:01:12,925 --> 00:01:14,155
Let's talk in person.

8
00:01:14,995 --> 00:01:15,995
Where are you?

9
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:18,065
I'm on the run, so I'm on the move.

10
00:01:18,626 --> 00:01:19,696
I'll send a car.

11
00:01:20,526 --> 00:01:21,666
You're alone, aren't you?

12
00:01:22,935 --> 00:01:23,935
Are you?

13
00:01:24,465 --> 00:01:25,535
Will you come alone?

14
00:01:27,135 --> 00:01:28,306
I'll text you.

15
00:01:34,846 --> 00:01:36,516
(Locker Service)

16
00:01:41,285 --> 00:01:43,854
(Women)

17
00:01:43,855 --> 00:01:46,185
The camera footage was programmed to be deleted.

18
00:01:46,726 --> 00:01:48,196
Was that your doing?

19
00:01:48,525 --> 00:01:49,525
Yes.

20
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:51,665
Did you give Lee Ro Um a pass?

21
00:01:52,195 --> 00:01:53,195
Yes.

22
00:01:53,766 --> 00:01:56,636
Na Su Ho. Was he in on it too?

23
00:01:57,335 --> 00:01:58,365
Yes.

24
00:02:00,565 --> 00:02:02,906
You could go away for this. Do you know that?

25
00:02:04,136 --> 00:02:05,175
Yes.

26
00:02:05,805 --> 00:02:07,106
What about Han Moo Young?

27
00:02:07,945 --> 00:02:09,615
He called you both here.

28
00:02:10,846 --> 00:02:12,915
You called us both in.

29
00:02:16,255 --> 00:02:17,485
We will...

30
00:02:17,486 --> 00:02:20,156
search your and Na's residences and seize all we can.

31
00:02:20,555 --> 00:02:22,025
We'll check your phones too.

32
00:02:24,356 --> 00:02:26,025
Don't smash your way in.

33
00:02:27,496 --> 00:02:28,895
Unlock the door with this.

34
00:02:29,335 --> 00:02:30,995
At the end of the hall past the toilet,

35
00:02:30,996 --> 00:02:32,936
you'll find a padlocked circuit breaker.

36
00:02:33,406 --> 00:02:34,606
Unlock that with this.

37
00:02:35,636 --> 00:02:37,136
Then flip the lever on the far left.

38
00:02:37,606 --> 00:02:39,346
That will get you into my workroom.

39
00:02:40,706 --> 00:02:42,145
You'll have to see it.

40
00:02:54,286 --> 00:02:56,455
The papers you gave me are the complete version...

41
00:02:56,456 --> 00:02:58,166
of what we found on Ji Seung Don.

42
00:02:59,226 --> 00:03:01,935
As we thought, it's the details of how Navis was laundering money.

43
00:03:03,965 --> 00:03:05,565
The company doing the deed...

44
00:03:05,566 --> 00:03:07,566
is Roman and Bay, a law firm in Panama.

45
00:03:08,175 --> 00:03:10,375
Their primary bank is B Bank in the Netherlands.

46
00:03:17,316 --> 00:03:20,046
I found the banker in charge of the president's funds.

47
00:03:20,316 --> 00:03:21,316
Kevin Ju.

48
00:03:21,585 --> 00:03:22,915
He's Korean-American,

49
00:03:22,916 --> 00:03:25,625
and he manages the accounts that are in Ji Seung Don's name.

50
00:03:32,365 --> 00:03:34,835
Ji Seung Don has five accounts.

51
00:03:35,066 --> 00:03:37,266
Three business and two personal accounts.

52
00:03:37,895 --> 00:03:39,635
Over 700 million dollars went through...

53
00:03:39,636 --> 00:03:41,506
these accounts in the past three years.

54
00:03:45,446 --> 00:03:48,075
As you see, all that money...

55
00:03:48,076 --> 00:03:50,675
ends up in one encoded account.

56
00:03:54,416 --> 00:03:55,786
Everything you see,

57
00:03:56,356 --> 00:03:59,125
the prosecutors will find when they search my place.

58
00:04:29,685 --> 00:04:31,385
Info on Navis Well-being...

59
00:04:31,386 --> 00:04:33,886
we got from Jang Kyung Ja's phone is in the Gray box.

60
00:04:34,585 --> 00:04:36,195
Roman and Bay's money-laundering...

61
00:04:36,196 --> 00:04:38,025
we tracked through that is in the blue box.

62
00:04:38,826 --> 00:04:40,364
Details on B Bank...

63
00:04:40,365 --> 00:04:42,465
and Kevin Ju are in the black box.

64
00:04:43,566 --> 00:04:45,335
Details on Jeokmok, the red box.

65
00:04:45,935 --> 00:04:48,305
Everything on Ji Seung Don, the white box.

66
00:05:00,516 --> 00:05:03,616
All five money-laundering accounts are in Ji Seung Don's name.

67
00:05:04,316 --> 00:05:07,255
Everything that's laundered ends up in a secret account...

68
00:05:07,256 --> 00:05:09,095
called F55.

69
00:05:09,256 --> 00:05:12,094
There's no way to find out who holds a secret account.

70
00:05:12,095 --> 00:05:14,795
Someone else holds the special drawing rights to Ji's accounts.

71
00:05:17,266 --> 00:05:18,835
And you're saying that's Jay?

72
00:05:19,665 --> 00:05:20,665
Yes.

73
00:05:21,105 --> 00:05:22,206
Where's the proof of that?

74
00:05:23,136 --> 00:05:24,376
Is that at your store too?

75
00:05:28,975 --> 00:05:30,376
As Jung Da Jung said,

76
00:05:30,746 --> 00:05:32,414
it's information on money laundering.

77
00:05:32,415 --> 00:05:33,816
Based on the statements,

78
00:05:34,016 --> 00:05:37,056
the biggest deposit they made in a month is over 200 million.

79
00:05:38,525 --> 00:05:41,426
We have enough to officially ask for account details.

80
00:05:43,095 --> 00:05:44,895
Then we'll only get Ji Seung Don.

81
00:05:45,696 --> 00:05:47,465
Or they could close all accounts by then.

82
00:05:52,866 --> 00:05:54,035
You said...

83
00:05:54,465 --> 00:05:56,505
we should find proof that points to the president...

84
00:05:56,506 --> 00:05:58,035
or a weapon to bargain with.

85
00:05:58,605 --> 00:05:59,876
I'm sorry this is it.

86
00:06:00,105 --> 00:06:02,576
I won't lie about you forcing me.

87
00:06:03,016 --> 00:06:05,715
I did it because I wanted to, so this is about us.

88
00:06:06,285 --> 00:06:08,915
Put an end to it and come back safely.

89
00:06:09,485 --> 00:06:10,915
I'll wait, Ro Um.

90
00:06:19,326 --> 00:06:20,966
(497 Nambu-ro 15-Gil, Seocheon-Gu, Seoul)

91
00:06:22,395 --> 00:06:24,335
(497 Nambu-ro 15-Gil, Seocheon-Gu, Seoul)

92
00:06:29,475 --> 00:06:31,975
If it's me the president wants...

93
00:06:32,605 --> 00:06:34,446
We do have some kind of weapon.

94
00:06:37,176 --> 00:06:38,386
It's not bad.

95
00:06:41,516 --> 00:06:43,516
I just have to risk my life.

96
00:07:26,696 --> 00:07:28,866
I thought you'd stop me from going alone.

97
00:07:39,105 --> 00:07:41,506
This is something you should put an end yourself.

98
00:07:42,076 --> 00:07:43,716
Something you can do and no one else can.

99
00:08:10,306 --> 00:08:13,206
Ro Um will meet Jay and get it herself.

100
00:08:13,645 --> 00:08:15,844
The evidence that Jay owns the account.

101
00:08:15,845 --> 00:08:16,876
What if she can't?

102
00:08:17,616 --> 00:08:20,284
Ms. Lee is still suspected of murdering Jang Kyung Ja.

103
00:08:20,285 --> 00:08:22,414
Besides, she's run off despite the arrest warrant.

104
00:08:22,415 --> 00:08:24,485
Do you know what this could cause?

105
00:08:25,285 --> 00:08:26,985
What can Ms. Lee do?

106
00:08:27,725 --> 00:08:30,196
The chances are really low that things will go as planned.

107
00:08:30,595 --> 00:08:32,315
You shouldn't do something this reckless...

108
00:08:32,426 --> 00:08:34,126
for that scarce possibility.

109
00:08:34,965 --> 00:08:37,335
If there had been another choice, we would've taken it.

110
00:08:37,766 --> 00:08:39,834
If Ro Um fails like you expect,

111
00:08:39,835 --> 00:08:40,965
it will be over for us.

112
00:08:41,465 --> 00:08:44,676
I wish the timing won't go off...

113
00:08:45,006 --> 00:08:47,075
I wish this will work no matter how tough it is...

114
00:08:47,076 --> 00:08:50,316
so that you can arrest her safely.

115
00:08:51,316 --> 00:08:54,215
So when she sends a signal,

116
00:08:54,816 --> 00:08:56,116
please be there in time.

117
00:08:59,585 --> 00:09:01,725
Keep sharing this location with the police.

118
00:09:02,256 --> 00:09:03,395
Where are you going?

119
00:09:04,126 --> 00:09:05,465
I need to go myself.

120
00:09:05,566 --> 00:09:07,046
Don't go anywhere, and stand by here.

121
00:09:07,225 --> 00:09:08,266
Stand by?

122
00:09:08,735 --> 00:09:11,965
Keep monitoring it as you leave footage.

123
00:09:13,006 --> 00:09:14,066
What...

124
00:10:07,156 --> 00:10:08,255
How did you escape?

125
00:10:09,125 --> 00:10:10,805
Check news reports when the morning comes.

126
00:10:11,995 --> 00:10:15,196
I prepared flight tickets, but I guess we won't get to ride it.

127
00:10:15,865 --> 00:10:18,196
You were to be released if you waited a little.

128
00:10:18,436 --> 00:10:19,906
Why were you so rushed?

129
00:10:20,005 --> 00:10:22,475
You mean, after you kill all the others.

130
00:10:24,776 --> 00:10:26,446
When did you grow so attached to them?

131
00:10:26,906 --> 00:10:30,146
You relied only on me in Jeokmok.

132
00:10:30,276 --> 00:10:32,146
And I paid the price for it.

133
00:10:34,416 --> 00:10:36,556
I don't understand.

134
00:10:36,956 --> 00:10:39,625
You're still hung up on your parents.

135
00:10:40,456 --> 00:10:42,354
Blood relationships mean nothing, Ro Um.

136
00:10:42,355 --> 00:10:44,125
It's not something you chose.

137
00:10:44,526 --> 00:10:46,665
You depended and trusted me...

138
00:10:46,666 --> 00:10:48,265
more than your family.

139
00:10:48,536 --> 00:10:50,296
Just as I chose you.

140
00:10:50,796 --> 00:10:52,906
This is what really matters.

141
00:10:55,406 --> 00:10:57,406
What exactly do you want from me?

142
00:10:57,576 --> 00:10:58,806
Replace Jang Kyung Ja?

143
00:11:00,505 --> 00:11:01,975
It's totally different.

144
00:11:02,176 --> 00:11:04,446
You'll come to understand soon.

145
00:11:06,316 --> 00:11:07,446
Where are we going?

146
00:11:08,485 --> 00:11:09,755
First, Hong Kong.

147
00:11:10,556 --> 00:11:11,786
When are we departing?

148
00:11:12,026 --> 00:11:14,156
I'm looking for a way to go there by ship.

149
00:11:21,995 --> 00:11:23,865
Then we'll have time to settle.

150
00:11:24,735 --> 00:11:27,964
You paid me before I left ten years ago.

151
00:11:27,965 --> 00:11:29,835
Do you need money? How much?

152
00:11:30,335 --> 00:11:32,776
How much did you make through Navis Well-being?

153
00:11:33,306 --> 00:11:35,416
News reports estimate it to be a billion dollars.

154
00:11:37,176 --> 00:11:38,276
What will you do with it?

155
00:11:38,646 --> 00:11:40,645
I'm going to give it back to who originally owned it.

156
00:11:40,646 --> 00:11:42,686
- Why? - Because I saw...

157
00:11:43,755 --> 00:11:44,786
the victims.

158
00:11:45,956 --> 00:11:47,926
Is this some sense of justice?

159
00:11:52,965 --> 00:11:54,926
I opened Jang Kyung Ja's safe.

160
00:11:56,335 --> 00:11:59,765
F55, the documents about your secret bank account.

161
00:12:00,706 --> 00:12:02,505
The evidence to prove that you own it.

162
00:12:03,635 --> 00:12:06,806
Those were in Ms. Jang's safe?

163
00:12:06,946 --> 00:12:09,946
You don't know what was in it.

164
00:12:10,776 --> 00:12:12,385
She told me everything.

165
00:12:12,916 --> 00:12:14,585
It had nothing about the secret account.

166
00:12:14,816 --> 00:12:16,615
Is that why you killed her?

167
00:12:17,255 --> 00:12:18,316
Because you believed her?

168
00:12:18,985 --> 00:12:20,656
She's gone now.

169
00:12:20,985 --> 00:12:23,595
I'm the only one who knows what was in it.

170
00:12:26,066 --> 00:12:29,465
If you got it, why did you come all the way here?

171
00:12:31,166 --> 00:12:34,406
I'm here to bargain with someone who'd buy it at the highest price.

172
00:12:35,375 --> 00:12:39,206
Around 300 million was deposited under Ji Seung Don's name, right?

173
00:12:40,446 --> 00:12:43,176
Consider it an advance and wire the money.

174
00:12:46,416 --> 00:12:49,816
Those documents are managed offline,

175
00:12:50,656 --> 00:12:52,926
so Ms. Jang had no access.

176
00:12:54,485 --> 00:12:55,495
You think...

177
00:12:56,225 --> 00:12:59,625
she collected them all alone?

178
00:13:00,926 --> 00:13:01,965
Figures.

179
00:13:02,735 --> 00:13:05,135
You never even checked her phone.

180
00:13:05,865 --> 00:13:09,835
Meanwhile, I remember your last text messages.

181
00:13:11,206 --> 00:13:14,406
Why suggest a trip to Sapporo when you were going to kill her?

182
00:13:16,146 --> 00:13:20,146
What? Are you finally sensing all this is possible?

183
00:13:23,615 --> 00:13:25,114
Wire the money,

184
00:13:25,115 --> 00:13:27,255
or do nothing and get arrested with me.

185
00:13:28,595 --> 00:13:29,625
It's up to you.

186
00:13:31,156 --> 00:13:32,265
Aren't you excited?

187
00:13:33,326 --> 00:13:34,865
You like making choices.

188
00:13:38,265 --> 00:13:43,605
The account number is N-1-7-8-B-A-N-K-0-9-1-0-3-1-3-1-7.

189
00:13:43,806 --> 00:13:45,105
Let's start with this.

190
00:13:45,475 --> 00:13:47,206
Around 130 million will do.

191
00:13:48,046 --> 00:13:50,416
I'll give you the second number in five minutes.

192
00:13:53,585 --> 00:13:56,156
It's a piece of cake to mobilize the men.

193
00:13:56,286 --> 00:13:59,426
It's a faraway country. How will you arrive in five minutes?

194
00:14:02,656 --> 00:14:06,365
I guess you still won't believe it unless you see it...

195
00:14:06,926 --> 00:14:07,926
for yourself.

196
00:14:09,166 --> 00:14:10,696
I trust Da Jung, you know.

197
00:14:27,916 --> 00:14:29,384
(Contacts)

198
00:14:29,385 --> 00:14:30,615
(Kevin Ju)

199
00:14:39,465 --> 00:14:41,796
I couldn't find any documents that had his name on them.

200
00:14:44,666 --> 00:14:48,205
What's important is, only one has been registered...

201
00:14:48,206 --> 00:14:50,036
to access these accounts online.

202
00:15:01,215 --> 00:15:04,786
I believe it's Jay's phone which has been off all along.

203
00:15:06,855 --> 00:15:08,624
Once his phone turns on,

204
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:11,526
I'll get the IP and MAC addresses through the Telecom service.

205
00:15:12,095 --> 00:15:13,925
If those match,

206
00:15:13,926 --> 00:15:15,766
an alarm will go off at the comic books place.

207
00:15:21,066 --> 00:15:22,835
It says a match, right?

208
00:15:25,845 --> 00:15:26,906
Yes.

209
00:15:27,475 --> 00:15:28,576
(Prosecutor Ryu Jae Hyuk)

210
00:15:30,646 --> 00:15:32,745
Yes, it's as Ms. Jung said.

211
00:15:33,385 --> 00:15:35,146
Lee Jay owns the account.

212
00:15:35,245 --> 00:15:37,855
No, at least it's enough to arrest him.

213
00:15:54,235 --> 00:15:55,306
You...

214
00:15:57,135 --> 00:15:59,146
needed my access history?

215
00:16:08,186 --> 00:16:10,786
Let me tell you why you're obsessed with me.

216
00:16:11,485 --> 00:16:13,985
You know what your nature is.

217
00:16:14,485 --> 00:16:15,685
What, the world abandoned you?

218
00:16:16,956 --> 00:16:19,895
Some people empathized with even the likes of me.

219
00:16:19,896 --> 00:16:21,265
I'm sure some did with you too.

220
00:16:22,026 --> 00:16:24,436
They must've approached and helped you with good intentions.

221
00:16:24,965 --> 00:16:26,665
You probably took that for granted,

222
00:16:26,666 --> 00:16:29,276
took away their everything, and threw them out.

223
00:16:30,735 --> 00:16:31,806
That's what you are like.

224
00:16:32,245 --> 00:16:34,375
You isolate yourself and fall behind.

225
00:16:34,706 --> 00:16:37,344
Violence or money is your only means to deal with people.

226
00:16:37,345 --> 00:16:39,686
Every moment, you're scared and suspicious...

227
00:16:39,816 --> 00:16:41,816
in case someone takes away what you have from you.

228
00:16:42,515 --> 00:16:44,885
I'm like you? Am I?

229
00:16:46,656 --> 00:16:48,156
It was your wishful thinking.

230
00:16:48,326 --> 00:16:50,655
Because you needed at least one more of someone like you...

231
00:16:50,656 --> 00:16:53,195
so you'd seem less hopeless and pathetic.

232
00:16:53,196 --> 00:16:55,635
So what?

233
00:16:55,765 --> 00:16:59,065
I'm not like you, you piece of trash!

234
00:16:59,066 --> 00:17:01,465
I was wrong about you?

235
00:17:02,135 --> 00:17:03,206
Is that right?

236
00:17:03,576 --> 00:17:04,875
For that long?

237
00:17:06,345 --> 00:17:07,505
It doesn't matter.

238
00:17:08,176 --> 00:17:10,046
I know you're a great actor.

239
00:17:10,646 --> 00:17:12,345
Act like somebody else and smile.

240
00:17:13,046 --> 00:17:15,615
You can keep doing that from now on for me.

241
00:17:17,115 --> 00:17:20,255
Da Jung, Na Sa, and Ring Go, and their families.

242
00:17:20,526 --> 00:17:23,326
I'll kill Moo Young and Jae Seok if I have to!

243
00:17:25,326 --> 00:17:27,725
Until you realize where you stand,

244
00:17:28,326 --> 00:17:29,864
and kneel before me,

245
00:17:29,865 --> 00:17:31,865
and never even think of putting your head up!

246
00:17:33,005 --> 00:17:35,265
I'll show them to you one by one.

247
00:17:36,436 --> 00:17:39,046
When you lose your mind, I'll lock you up and watch.

248
00:17:40,005 --> 00:17:42,646
If you die, I'll even take your ashes!

249
00:17:43,146 --> 00:17:44,816
You can never get away from me.

250
00:17:47,015 --> 00:17:48,085
Kill me.

251
00:17:49,315 --> 00:17:51,285
That will make things way easier.

252
00:19:34,086 --> 00:19:36,255
Ro Um has been arrested.

253
00:19:41,926 --> 00:19:43,065
Does that mean...

254
00:19:43,965 --> 00:19:45,565
that she's alive?

255
00:19:47,166 --> 00:19:48,166
Yes.

256
00:19:48,836 --> 00:19:50,176
Jay was the one who got shot.

257
00:19:56,946 --> 00:19:59,045
He's not dead, is he?

258
00:19:59,815 --> 00:20:00,846
I mean,

259
00:20:01,586 --> 00:20:04,186
Ro Um didn't commit murder, right?

260
00:20:07,285 --> 00:20:10,755
Ro Um is still the suspect of Jang Kyung Ja's murder.

261
00:20:11,126 --> 00:20:12,465
The one who shot him...

262
00:20:12,896 --> 00:20:14,295
was her lawyer.

263
00:20:14,965 --> 00:20:15,965
What?

264
00:20:16,295 --> 00:20:18,336
(Police)

265
00:20:34,815 --> 00:20:37,335
You have evidence that proves that Jay is the president, right?

266
00:20:37,456 --> 00:20:38,785
Is that your concern right now?

267
00:20:39,285 --> 00:20:40,325
What about Ro Um?

268
00:20:42,525 --> 00:20:44,025
Worry about yourself.

269
00:20:45,426 --> 00:20:46,765
She's fine.

270
00:21:01,706 --> 00:21:02,916
