271
00:21:03,646 --> 00:21:04,715
It's a beginning.

272
00:21:05,676 --> 00:21:06,715
That's true.

273
00:21:07,146 --> 00:21:08,446
Thanks to you,

274
00:21:08,715 --> 00:21:10,555
I have truckloads of issues to deal with.

275
00:21:12,156 --> 00:21:13,796
It sounds like you should be celebrating.

276
00:21:14,886 --> 00:21:15,995
It's a jackpot.

277
00:21:16,255 --> 00:21:17,255
Gosh.

278
00:21:18,025 --> 00:21:19,926
You're certainly outcome-oriented.

279
00:21:20,396 --> 00:21:23,396
You said that you also wanted to change the outcome.

280
00:21:25,166 --> 00:21:26,706
Now, it's your turn.

281
00:21:27,235 --> 00:21:28,436
I'll leave it to you.

282
00:21:30,805 --> 00:21:32,676
Because I never want to come back to this.

283
00:21:36,315 --> 00:21:37,775
- Take her away. - Yes, sir.

284
00:21:39,346 --> 00:21:40,346
Let's go.

285
00:21:42,856 --> 00:21:44,514
These are the materials confiscated from Jung,

286
00:21:44,515 --> 00:21:47,625
the accomplice to the escape from the Prosecutions' Service.

287
00:21:47,626 --> 00:21:50,355
From a foundation established in the 1990s...

288
00:21:50,356 --> 00:21:51,855
to the Navisgate,

289
00:21:51,856 --> 00:21:55,725
these files include the incidents of the past 20 years.

290
00:21:57,366 --> 00:21:58,764
Your closest personal,

291
00:21:58,765 --> 00:22:01,366
also known as the Messenger, Kim Seung Hyun.

292
00:22:01,735 --> 00:22:03,676
And the anchor, Kevin Ju.

293
00:22:04,106 --> 00:22:06,744
They've been arrested, and we got their warrants.

294
00:22:06,745 --> 00:22:08,745
They both confessed.

295
00:22:09,275 --> 00:22:10,475
And as you know,

296
00:22:10,916 --> 00:22:13,785
you're the leader of Jeokmok...

297
00:22:14,146 --> 00:22:15,586
and the owner of Navis Well-being.

298
00:22:15,985 --> 00:22:18,215
Do you admit that you're the president?

299
00:22:22,596 --> 00:22:24,754
It will be tiresome to lengthen the questioning.

300
00:22:24,755 --> 00:22:27,495
You don't seem to be in the best condition either.

301
00:22:28,166 --> 00:22:29,465
Will you not confess?

302
00:22:33,065 --> 00:22:34,165
Fine.

303
00:22:34,166 --> 00:22:35,206
Then,

304
00:22:36,106 --> 00:22:39,175
let's begin with the murder of Ms. Jang Kyung Ja.

305
00:22:39,176 --> 00:22:42,244
Han was caught in the act of using firearms...

306
00:22:42,245 --> 00:22:44,445
to subdue Lee on the scene and was arrested.

307
00:22:44,446 --> 00:22:46,885
He's currently being interrogated without detention...

308
00:22:46,886 --> 00:22:48,761
for violating the Gun Control Act causing bodily harm.

309
00:22:48,785 --> 00:22:51,386
Are you saying that you intended all of it?

310
00:22:52,356 --> 00:22:53,784
Because I've seen...

311
00:22:53,785 --> 00:22:55,856
what type of man Jay was and what he had done.

312
00:22:56,495 --> 00:22:58,096
I figured that I'd need a gun.

313
00:22:59,666 --> 00:23:02,196
How did you know they were there?

314
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:05,835
I was the one who led Ro Um's escape.

315
00:23:05,836 --> 00:23:08,336
I also helped her escape.

316
00:23:39,206 --> 00:23:40,464
These are the past decisions...

317
00:23:40,465 --> 00:23:42,335
of non-indictment by Prosecutor Choi.

318
00:23:42,336 --> 00:23:43,376
Thanks.

319
00:23:45,836 --> 00:23:47,044
I looked into it,

320
00:23:47,045 --> 00:23:50,176
and he seemed to be the type to analyze the situation in detail.

321
00:23:50,846 --> 00:23:52,685
Our case might be complicated,

322
00:23:52,686 --> 00:23:55,744
but I reckoned it'd be better to tell him the exact circumstances.

323
00:23:55,745 --> 00:23:56,784
In the standard fashion.

324
00:23:56,785 --> 00:23:58,215
During the trial, Moo Young...

325
00:24:02,356 --> 00:24:03,856
Let's get the written opinion done.

326
00:24:06,065 --> 00:24:07,126
Hey.

327
00:24:09,636 --> 00:24:12,606
I think they're having a hard time due to lack of evidence.

328
00:24:13,005 --> 00:24:14,711
The security footage has been deleted as well.

329
00:24:14,735 --> 00:24:16,176
But he was caught red-handed.

330
00:24:16,575 --> 00:24:18,074
I'm sure they'll connect him to helping the escape.

331
00:24:18,075 --> 00:24:21,045
They'll indict him for conspiring with Ro Um.

332
00:24:21,275 --> 00:24:24,175
But it's likely to be declined for lack of evidence,

333
00:24:24,176 --> 00:24:26,457
so they'll try to get everything they can connect to her.

334
00:24:27,416 --> 00:24:29,186
Here. The interrogation file.

335
00:24:30,555 --> 00:24:31,656
I'll copy them.

336
00:24:34,686 --> 00:24:36,196
Just tell them that I didn't do it.

337
00:24:36,725 --> 00:24:39,025
You'll be at a disadvantage if you deny all of them.

338
00:24:42,565 --> 00:24:44,535
They say that the Messenger talked.

339
00:24:45,096 --> 00:24:46,106
Is that true?

340
00:24:49,206 --> 00:24:50,405
Where's Baek Ho?

341
00:24:50,406 --> 00:24:52,646
Do you know how much he got from this?

342
00:24:52,775 --> 00:24:55,176
None of them can help you.

343
00:24:55,275 --> 00:24:57,775
Nor will they run into you in the courtroom.

344
00:24:58,916 --> 00:25:01,446
I had been building my credit for 20 years.

345
00:25:01,745 --> 00:25:04,092
And you want me to believe that no one will testify for me?

346
00:25:04,116 --> 00:25:05,616
We can't claim innocence.

347
00:25:05,956 --> 00:25:08,156
You must admit to a few crimes...

348
00:25:08,325 --> 00:25:09,926
to get a reduced sentence.

349
00:25:10,696 --> 00:25:12,025
This is a tough situation.

350
00:25:12,426 --> 00:25:14,565
So, make the situation easier.

351
00:25:15,465 --> 00:25:17,436
That is why I'm paying you.

352
00:25:17,965 --> 00:25:19,465
This trial is not the end.

353
00:25:19,936 --> 00:25:22,635
I heard that you've replaced five attorneys.

354
00:25:22,636 --> 00:25:25,005
But your charges are too extensive.

355
00:25:25,336 --> 00:25:26,951
You must brace yourself for prolonged war.

356
00:25:26,975 --> 00:25:28,545
You've decided to have faith in us,

357
00:25:29,045 --> 00:25:30,376
so we need your trust.

358
00:25:31,075 --> 00:25:32,075
"Trust?"

359
00:25:32,916 --> 00:25:33,946
"Have faith?"

360
00:25:36,686 --> 00:25:37,755
In you?

361
00:25:40,055 --> 00:25:41,456
We'll lose in the trial.

362
00:25:42,856 --> 00:25:45,225
But it was self-defence. You didn't even kill him.

363
00:25:45,356 --> 00:25:47,876
I could be sentenced to three years just for carrying firearms.

364
00:25:48,096 --> 00:25:50,065
It's more than enough to disbar me.

365
00:25:51,936 --> 00:25:53,336
You knew that?

366
00:25:54,336 --> 00:25:55,336
I did.

367
00:25:55,565 --> 00:25:56,935
What were you thinking?

368
00:25:56,936 --> 00:25:59,176
You were in danger. I didn't have the time to think.

369
00:26:02,376 --> 00:26:04,146
Tell them that I had the gun.

370
00:26:04,275 --> 00:26:05,975
And pin the blame on you?

371
00:26:06,186 --> 00:26:08,215
When I had done it? Like a coward?

372
00:26:08,686 --> 00:26:10,784
Or say that Jay dropped it.

373
00:26:10,785 --> 00:26:13,156
Tell them it was his gun. It's not exactly false.

374
00:26:14,356 --> 00:26:16,626
I did have it on me,

375
00:26:17,096 --> 00:26:18,225
so that'd be perjury.

376
00:26:19,696 --> 00:26:21,764
How are you so inflexible?

377
00:26:21,765 --> 00:26:23,366
You let that gun go.

378
00:26:23,666 --> 00:26:26,265
That's what kept Jay alive so that he could be punished by law.

379
00:26:26,936 --> 00:26:28,406
This is worth it.

380
00:26:29,265 --> 00:26:30,865
Otherwise, I'll be damaging the value...

381
00:26:31,005 --> 00:26:32,946
of the hard-earned trial.

382
00:26:33,446 --> 00:26:35,406
So, you're just going to give up?

383
00:26:37,215 --> 00:26:39,176
My lawyer will write a statement.

384
00:26:39,715 --> 00:26:42,916
The prosecutor will read it and decide...

385
00:26:43,285 --> 00:26:44,886
whether to prosecute me or not.

386
00:26:48,926 --> 00:26:50,126
Is he a good lawyer?

387
00:26:54,926 --> 00:26:58,065
Our firm is preparing to defend you in court.

388
00:26:58,366 --> 00:26:59,706
You don't need to worry about it.

389
00:27:10,215 --> 00:27:11,275
Hello.

390
00:27:14,315 --> 00:27:15,785
Take your pick. You're hard at work.

391
00:27:16,045 --> 00:27:17,656
Thank you.

392
00:27:21,426 --> 00:27:22,896
- Let me... - Leave it.

393
00:27:23,356 --> 00:27:24,426
Thanks.

394
00:27:26,096 --> 00:27:28,695
- Thank you. - It's nothing.

395
00:27:28,696 --> 00:27:31,095
Oh, the lawyer you're prosecuting.

396
00:27:31,096 --> 00:27:33,004
The other charges won't stick,

397
00:27:33,005 --> 00:27:35,166
but you have him on possessing a firearm.

398
00:27:36,475 --> 00:27:37,974
Yes. I'm considering that.

399
00:27:37,975 --> 00:27:39,504
Jay gave that gun...

400
00:27:39,505 --> 00:27:41,445
to Lee Ro Um to kill someone else.

401
00:27:41,446 --> 00:27:44,474
And she left it with her lawyer to return it.

402
00:27:44,475 --> 00:27:46,445
But he must've reached for it...

403
00:27:46,446 --> 00:27:48,285
because his client was in danger.

404
00:27:48,386 --> 00:27:50,314
You were at the scene, right?

405
00:27:50,315 --> 00:27:53,025
I was, and it was a dreadful sight.

406
00:27:53,186 --> 00:27:55,856
I hate to think what would've happened if he hadn't been there.

407
00:27:55,985 --> 00:27:58,294
Jay would've killed Lee and fled,

408
00:27:58,295 --> 00:28:00,795
and the public would bury us for losing the culprit.

409
00:28:01,396 --> 00:28:04,395
The more the public hears about the case,

410
00:28:04,396 --> 00:28:05,835
the worse it is for us.

411
00:28:05,836 --> 00:28:08,964
If you want to charge the guy, you'd better steel yourself.

412
00:28:08,965 --> 00:28:10,535
You might get shot down too.

413
00:28:10,975 --> 00:28:13,706
Okay. I'll look over the papers carefully.

414
00:28:14,406 --> 00:28:15,645
You know what to do.

415
00:28:15,646 --> 00:28:17,415
When you're done with this,

416
00:28:17,416 --> 00:28:19,176
how about joining Special Investigations?

417
00:28:19,485 --> 00:28:22,215
Jay's a jackpot for us, and I need some good men.

418
00:28:22,886 --> 00:28:24,956
You heard we're expanding, right?

419
00:28:26,656 --> 00:28:28,686
Think about it. Enjoy the soda.

420
00:28:31,325 --> 00:28:33,396
- By the way, sir. - Yes?

421
