473
00:32:29,292 --> 00:32:31,402
For the previously stated reasons, Na Su Ho is charged with...

474
00:32:31,403 --> 00:32:33,632
aiding escape, and the promotion of information...

475
00:32:33,633 --> 00:32:36,033
and communication network use and protection of information.

476
00:32:36,302 --> 00:32:39,042
How do you know the defendants?

477
00:32:40,042 --> 00:32:42,612
When I was in medical school, I took part...

478
00:32:42,613 --> 00:32:44,581
in a study involving the defendants.

479
00:32:44,582 --> 00:32:45,812
What was it about?

480
00:32:46,383 --> 00:32:49,353
We studied the educational background of gifted children.

481
00:32:49,582 --> 00:32:52,082
Alternative schooling as opposed to home schooling.

482
00:32:52,423 --> 00:32:55,653
I didn't know at the time, but that foundation was Jeokmok.

483
00:32:56,292 --> 00:32:59,663
Did you meet the defendants since they came of age?

484
00:33:00,133 --> 00:33:01,831
I visited them much later...

485
00:33:01,832 --> 00:33:04,162
to apologize, after I found out about Jeokmok.

486
00:33:04,163 --> 00:33:06,203
Why did you want to apologize?

487
00:33:07,072 --> 00:33:09,402
Because no children should ever be raised...

488
00:33:09,403 --> 00:33:11,342
in those conditions.

489
00:33:11,343 --> 00:33:15,042
The study I took part in contributed to creating Jeokmok Kids.

490
00:33:16,312 --> 00:33:18,113
I felt guilty.

491
00:33:18,883 --> 00:33:20,812
As a psychiatrist,

492
00:33:21,413 --> 00:33:24,982
do you have an opinion on what the defendants did?

493
00:33:26,252 --> 00:33:28,521
The defendants had no protector...

494
00:33:28,522 --> 00:33:30,262
within the Jeokmok group.

495
00:33:30,822 --> 00:33:32,692
They were given orders, not instructions,

496
00:33:32,693 --> 00:33:34,732
and to survive, they'd have had to obey.

497
00:33:35,032 --> 00:33:36,862
Their values would've been distorted,

498
00:33:36,863 --> 00:33:40,103
and as adults, they'd have struggled to lead normal lives.

499
00:33:41,232 --> 00:33:43,403
Despite that, the defendants...

500
00:33:44,843 --> 00:33:47,012
seem to have become each other's protector.

501
00:33:47,812 --> 00:33:49,173
To protect others,

502
00:33:49,542 --> 00:33:52,443
they used what they'd learned and what they were used to.

503
00:33:53,113 --> 00:33:55,653
I think that was their only option.

504
00:33:56,283 --> 00:33:59,723
Do you wish to say the defendants aren't criminals?

505
00:34:00,153 --> 00:34:02,993
I'm not saying they didn't do wrong.

506
00:34:03,423 --> 00:34:04,762
I'm saying...

507
00:34:04,763 --> 00:34:08,133
they could've made different choices if it hadn't been for Jeokmok.

508
00:34:08,263 --> 00:34:11,133
Not even a doctor could be sure of that.

509
00:34:12,332 --> 00:34:16,033
We can't say because you nor I have been through it.

510
00:34:16,173 --> 00:34:18,541
I only gave my opinion...

511
00:34:18,542 --> 00:34:21,371
on why they had to break the law...

512
00:34:21,372 --> 00:34:23,013
to achieve their goal.

513
00:34:23,113 --> 00:34:25,481
Our past experiences...

514
00:34:25,482 --> 00:34:27,482
influence how we make a choice.

515
00:34:28,082 --> 00:34:29,513
Even if it's wrong,

516
00:34:29,883 --> 00:34:33,153
not everyone always makes the moral or legal choice.

517
00:34:33,693 --> 00:34:36,823
You have a scary way of justifying crimes.

518
00:34:37,522 --> 00:34:39,932
I'm not trying to justify crimes.

519
00:34:40,732 --> 00:34:42,792
That's the judge's decision.

520
00:34:44,033 --> 00:34:47,473
I just want to say the lives they led...

521
00:34:48,033 --> 00:34:52,041
gave me clues that allow me to understand them.

522
00:34:52,042 --> 00:34:53,713
That's all.

523
00:35:03,723 --> 00:35:04,783
Are you nervous?

524
00:35:05,752 --> 00:35:07,852
- About what? - The sentencing?

525
00:35:08,493 --> 00:35:11,093
We will try, but you might get sent away.

526
00:35:12,923 --> 00:35:13,993
Not really.

527
00:35:14,763 --> 00:35:17,102
I even stood trial for something I didn't do.

528
00:35:19,002 --> 00:35:21,372
This time, it's for something I did do.

529
00:35:22,573 --> 00:35:23,642
More than anything,

530
00:35:24,602 --> 00:35:26,173
I trust my lawyer.

531
00:35:31,482 --> 00:35:32,743
Make your final statement.

532
00:35:33,713 --> 00:35:34,852
The defendants,

533
00:35:35,213 --> 00:35:37,883
to get through a situation in which their lives were at stake,

534
00:35:38,352 --> 00:35:40,693
planned to escape the Prosecutors' Office,

535
00:35:40,852 --> 00:35:42,351
and in the process,

536
00:35:42,352 --> 00:35:44,093
